Package: python3-anthropic
Architecture: all
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 ${python3:Depends},
Description: official Python client for the Anthropic API (Avalan PPA pin)
 The anthropic SDK provides typed Python bindings for the Anthropic
 Messages API plus async / sync transports, response streaming, and
 a Bedrock / Vertex integration shim. Avalan ships it in its
 `vendors` extra at `>= 0.71, < 0.72`; Debian sid carries 0.91.x
 (above the ceiling), so the rebuild pins 0.71.1.
 .
 The optional `jiter` Rust accelerator is intentionally not declared
 as a Depends -- it lives behind a lazy `from jiter import from_json`
 inside the streaming-tool-input delta handler, so the bulk of the
 SDK works without it. Callers exercising that specific path get an
 ImportError telling them to `pip install jiter` into a venv.
